PUBLIC HEALTH COMPLAINT (PHC) - SOFTWARE PRODUCT LINE (SPL)


ABOUT PHC
Check the Public Health Complaint SPL website [http://www.ic.unicamp.br/~tizzei/phc/] for more informations about this system.


LICENSE
Please, read the license MITLicense.txt in the $PHC-HOME directory.


INSTALATION
1) Setup the variables in the ./src/publichealthcomplaint/datatypes/Constants.java according to your system configuration. 


EXECUTION
1) Build the PHCS: <$PHC-HOME> ant build.xml
2) Execute the Java EE server you like. For instance, if you are using glassfish, run: <$GLASSFISH-HOME>/bin/asadmin start-domain domains/domain1
3) Execute the RMI registry: <$PHC-HOME/bats/> sh registry.sh
4) Open the address in your browser (for glassfish): http://localhost:4848/
5) Deploy the war file generate after the execution of the step 1. Add the path to all libraries separated by comma in the "Libraries" field. Click on "OK".
6) Click on "launch"
